                        <msContents>
                            <summary>
                                <p>According to Matthew Norris, the first text <quote xml:lang="la">Commentarius de linguis variarum gentium</quote> is a Latin translation of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100544">Johannes Bureus</persName>’s treatise <quote xml:lang="sv">Afhandling om språkens upkomst och skrifart</quote> (Treatise on the Origin and Writing of Languages). In the only surviving copy of the treatise (<ref target="http://urn.kb.se/resolve?urn=urn:nbn:se:alvin:portal:record-12520">Linköping Diocesan Library, Spr. 1 fol.</ref>), text at the end is missing that is present in the Latin translation.</p>
                            </summary>
